##They began a 24-hour battle for vegetables

Editor | Xiao Zhu

"It's in my hand. "

Li Xiaolin is pushing a tricycle with a basket full of cucumbers. It has just been picked for two days and is still green. He pushed the cart to the side of the village garbage ditch, removed the cucumbers from the cart, and emptied them into the ditch.

Four or five days after the end of the year, he estimated that a total of tens of thousands of pounds of cucumber dumped, lost tens of thousands of dollars, he was distressed and uncomfortable, "pour is money, is hard-earned money. ". "The former villagers of Xibu village in Yantai, Shandong Province, where he lives, grow cucumbers for a living. Every family falls down. The cucumbers in the ditches are piled up into mountains. The daughter-in-law of a neighbor's family hides at home and cries secretly, li Xiaolin felt that the whole village was dead.

The first month was originally the peak season of cucumber sales, sales volume, high prices, summer sales of one or two yuan a catty, the first month can be sold to four or five yuan, this month's income can account for more than half of the year. Li Xiaolin is looking forward to selling more this Spring Festival. He has planted four large-shed cucumbers, which ripen about 2,000 kilograms each day. He picks them, and puts them into the warehouse by basket and by yard. He is afraid that the cucumbers will be frozen, and he carefully covers the layers with quilts, waiting for the greengrocers to come into the village and haul them away. However, a sudden epidemic destroyed all his ideas.

After the Lunar New Year's Eve, Li Xiaolin found that the sliding door at the entrance of the village was locked. People from the village had to register to enter and exit. People and vehicles from the outside village were not allowed to enter. At this time of year, vegetable buyers who were bustling around were also shut out.

"If the buyers can't get in, if the farmers can't sell, then the cucumbers rot at home. "Li Xiaolin said. He thought of a number of ways, in the village stalls, contact the city's supermarket, but the front method can not sell, the latter tried to enter the village. The cucumbers in the greenhouse are still growing and maturing, and the ones in the greenhouses are still fresh and look good. One by one they are hanging on the branches. Li Xiaolin is very anxious to see them. He doesn't even know whether he should pick them again. Let's take them off, they won't sell, and it's a waste of manpower to pull them into his home, i had to dump it somewhere close by. Do Not Pick it, these melons will be old, and then grow down to affect the next crop of cucumber growth. "There's nothing you can do about it. You just let all that time go by. "He said.

A picture of a cucumber at Li Xiaolin's house

When Li Xiaolin was struggling, Cheng Shuo, a villager from Dacheng Village, 150 km away, was in a similar predicament. When he was twenty-eight, he noticed that a red line had been drawn at the entrance of the village. A few days later, the red line was replaced by a car that would never let anyone leave. A few cadres in the village built a small shed, take turns on duty, a day a night, eat and sleep in the shed, do not let outsiders in.

Dacheng village grows Leeks for a living. Cheng Shuo's family grows four mu of LEEKS. They plan to cut their heads after the new year. In previous years, it was local small traders who came into the village to collect leeks. Sometimes they deliberately underbid their prices, and it is not uncommon for them to default on their money, but it was the only way to sell the leeks in the village, and the villagers were honest and sold without any effort. Cheng Shuo planned to sell the land for 40,000 or 50,000 yuan per mu, which was the entire annual income of the rural family, but the only channel was completely cut off years later.

LEEKS and other vegetables are not the same, to grow quickly cut, long too high leaves will fall in rows, never up, means that this leek is finished. Cut is also very difficult, Leek damp, the root of the soil can not put two days, do not sell began to rot.

Cheng Shuo remembered that this crop of Chinese chives had been planted since May last year. In July and August, little green plants grew up. He transplanted the young plants one by one into the big shed, carefully fertilizing, watering... These money and time look to be lost, the home was shrouded in a cloud, eat New Year's Eve dinner, the family is quiet, food does not taste. My mother, who was in her fifties and had a mouth full of bubbles, spent several days in bed.

The village has more serious than Chengshuo family, a family planted more than 10 mu of Leek, cut and sold, put in the home white rot, "a year without income, the family cry every day. ". "sung-seok said. The whole village was in despair. "I thought the Leek was finished, and I smashed it. ". "

Chinese chives that no one cares about

"The lonely Walker. "

The turnaround came a week later.

The Taobao Foodie project team found the plight of Li Xiaolin and Cheng Shuo, as well as countless Li Xiaolin and Cheng Shuo across the country. In order to help these farmers, Taobao eats food only 12 hours on-line "eat food to help farmers" channel, the first selection of six provinces in Shandong, Sichuan, Zhejiang, Liaoning and other 10 unsalable quality agricultural products. The day before the launch, Gong Mengqian, a newcomer and post-1990s girl from Jiangxi Province who is in charge of the operation of the vegetable industry, spent the whole day on the phone with the vendors of the vegetable industry to communicate about the launch of the product.

She found Mengqiang's flagship store, which had $100 million in online revenue last year. The founders, Guo Jing and Guo Jing, are in their early 30s, born in the countryside and selling mostly fruit and vegetables. Guo Jing had hoped he would finally be able to take a few days off for the New Year, but the outbreak has thrown everything out of whack.

She asked Guo Jing, "would you like to try some leafy Greens? " . In the past, they had only tomatoes, pumpkins or sweet potatoes that were easy to store and easy to transport. They were afraid to try some of the more difficult green leafy vegetables.

This time, Guo Jing said "dare. " . His parents, growing cucumbers, also encountered a difficult situation of slow sales. He saw the price of cucumbers in the supermarket rise from 4 yuan to 10 yuan per catty. "In fact, there is no problem on the supply side and there is no problem on the demand side, except that the transportation chain in the middle is broken, i'm feeling very sick. Guo Jing's family grew vegetables and sold them themselves, so he had a double role. "He wanted people like me who lived in the city to eat them, but he also wanted his parents to sell them, so this year I made up my mind to do it. "

They began a round-the-clock battle for vegetables.

He and Cheng sifted through a few unmarketable vegetables, including cucumbers, tomatoes, radishes, cabbages and Leeks, before driving a five-metre-long truck to villages within 200 kilometres of Yantai. Their shop, which had previously exported fruit and was well qualified, finally got a rare pass from the local government after a complicated approval process.

When Chengshuo first met Chengkelong, he came to the village to see the Leeks. After seeing several of the Leeks, he introduced the Taobao activities to everyone and said, "you cut, we'll take all the LEEKS. ". " Cheng Shuo's mother, a village cadre, immediately went to the village branch to make a broadcast over a loudspeaker. "someone came to buy leeks! "The villagers ran out of their homes in a great hurry.

Chengshuo remember, at that time the villagers do not expect to earn much money, even if money also want to sell, do not put in the home rotten heartache. But Cheng Kelong did not drive down the price, per catty acquisition price than the offline acquisition of more than 10 or 20 cents, he repeatedly told the villagers impatient, "everyone take it easy, will give everyone out. ". "

On the day of receiving the news, the gloom in Cheng Shuo's home was lifted. His mother cooked a hearty meal of oily fish and stewed vegetables at noon. "They really helped. ". "

From the New Year, Guo Jing and Chan's day started at 3 am. The first thing they did when they got up was to call and check with the farmers one by one whether the dishes were ready. If they were, they dressed and washed as quickly as possible, grab some last night's leftovers or some instant noodles, and head out in the truck.

Even with a pass, the journey is often as difficult as a game. At highway junctions they are often stopped, and the farming villages are sometimes joined together, the innermost being the most difficult. "If you have to cross several cards, and one of them is impassable, you can't cross it. " The hardest thing for Guo Jing was when the farmer called and told him, "the vegetables aren't coming. "The other side's tone is anxious, he is also uncomfortable, but all has no way.

In unfamiliar villages, they are often driven away by hostility and have to park their trucks farther away. Guo Jing could also sense the mixed feelings of the villagers who had imposed the blockade. "They welcome US and they don't welcome us. They don't welcome us for fear of infection. We welcome them because we are here to solve their urgent problem. How can we live in spring without selling our vegetables? "? "

Later, they came up with the solution is to let the villagers put vegetables to the entrance of the village, Cheng Kelong up weighing, calculating, from the alipay to transfer money to them, and then move the vegetable basket to the truck. This is not the place to stay long, the two sides nodded their heads far away and left in a hurry. "You feel like you're working underground. "We're like a couple of farmers, " Guo Jing says with a smile. "The farmers want to sell, we want to buy, it's the epidemic that keeps US apart, but we're attracted to each other. " (laughter). "

Li Xiaolin's village also did not let Cheng Kelong into the beginning, Cheng Kelong went to the township government to do a variety of dredging and efforts, finally can drive into the village, Li Xiaolin family watched the family cucumber truck away, long out of breath, relieved. Originally, the family of the elderly are reluctant to buy even vegetables, now also willing to buy some fish and meat.

At the end of the day, Guo Jing and Chan travel to about 20 villages, thousands of kilometers a day, hauling back seven or eight tons of vegetables and carrying baskets to their carts thousands of times. They do not have time to eat, drink water in the high intensity of labor is almost exhausted, hardly go to the toilet. They had to rush back in the afternoon before the delivery car arrived, and Guo Jing could feel his eyes burning as he drove, so he had to drink a lot of red bull to keep his spirits up. He couldn't hold on much longer, he had to stop for a while, get Out of the car, take a few puffs of the cold air, freeze for a while, wake up, and drive on.

There were few cars on the road, and the city seemed to have hit the pause button. All Guo Jing could see were police cars, ambulances, construction trucks and, occasionally, fire trucks. Guo Jing didn't like the cars, and their presence alone seemed to indicate that something bad had happened. "We don't want to see these cars, " he said. "We want to see private cars bustling about, driving with ordinary people. "

At that moment, he would feel lonely. "I used to feel like I was living in a noisy metropolis, but now I feel like I'm running by myself, like a lonely Walker, so close and so far away from others, we don't know how long this outbreak will last. "

They may be sustained by a few small moments. Shing remembers a time when he went to Shouguang to collect rape. After carrying a farmer's rape to the car, the two sides said goodbye. The farmer was in his 60s and dressed in plain clothes. He looked at Cheng with almost begging eyes. "When will you come again? "? I have a lot of rape at home, and then the old, worthless. "I'll be back soon, don't worry. ". "

I just want to help them sell their vegetables and do my best to help them. "said Cheng.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Cheng kelong fills his stomach with instant noodles in a leek field

"Hang in there. Hang in there till this thing blows over. "

Bringing it home is not the end. Platform in order to ensure the rights and interests of consumers, require businesses to do within 48 hours of delivery.

The LEEKS need to be watered down for the newspaper, the cucumbers need to be wrapped in Pearl cotton, the tomatoes need to be stuffed into plastic columns, the potatoes need to be netted one by one... even though Guo Jing has expanded his team of 30 to more than 100, that's not enough. According to the management measures during the epidemic period, they can not gather together to work, only three or five people can be divided into a small group packing.

Even more difficult is the fact that most of the carton factories have not returned to work. They have scoured the world for cartons, stock from the carton factories, boxes sold to the distilleries, boxes from the milk factories, and anything that is clean and unused, they will take it. In an interview with "people" reporters, Cheng Kelong has been looking for a day's box, but the results of a few, the interview did not last too long, he hastily hung up the phone, to continue to find.

Some farmers, knowing they were short-handed, asked Guo Jing to deliver the bales. "We'll pack them up for you. You can just pull them away. "Guo Jing tried to pay for the farmers'packages, one dollar at a time, but the farmers refused. Some farmers sell out of their own vegetables, and help him find other sources, midnight 11,12 am still helping him contact. Back and forth used to be a business, but now you suddenly feel the unadorned warmth of helping each other in this time of crisis. "

Since the launch of help the farmers eat, orders at Guo Jing's and Cheng Kelong's have surged even further than singles'day, with up to four hundred vegetable orders a day now selling more than 100,000 at most, the shipment, which weighs nearly one million pounds a day, comes from people who can not go out to buy vegetables under the closed control of the outbreak. "You feel like people are going crazy to eat vegetables. "said Guo Jing.

Gong Mengqian also saw that this period of time the whole Amoy vegetables category of small businesses grow very fast, online selling vegetables are usually not five Jin or three kilograms, combined packaging, the way is very popular cycle purchase. In her communication, these businesses began to expand more categories, such as toona sinensis seasonal dishes have more merchants to choose from.

But the merchants did not sell these hard-won vegetables at high prices, Li Xiaolin went to the Mengqiang flagship store page to see, "they sell a lot, but the price is not high, very popular. ". " Guo Jing explains why, in his experience, prices go up for just a few days a year. "We know it's short-lived, it goes down to a normal level in a few days, and you just raise the price for four or five days. You may adjust prices with the market, but when it comes to bulk goods, a little less or a little loss is still OK, it really can not bear others will rise, I can still hold. "He said.

Guo Jing slept only four or five hours a day, and when he got home, he closed his eyes on the couch, barely able to undress. He often feels tired and his limbs ache, but he thinks he has to carry on. "You're racing against the clock, you're racing against your strength, you say you don't have that much, and if you don't, you're going to have to suffer. You can legally take the vegetables from the farmers, you can serve them to everyone, if you have the ability, you have to do it, if your body can not bear it in the future, then you won't do it, but if I can still do it now, I hope I can last longer, until the outbreak is over. "

In the week since its launch, Taobao has sold 18,000 tonnes of produce. On February 13, Taobao announced the establishment of a $1 billion fund to help farmers sell off the country's unsold agricultural products and implement 10 measures to help farmers, these include the launch of the "love to help farmers special line" (nail number: Aixinzhunong) to collect information on slow-selling agricultural products, the launch of a series of special zones on Taobao for agricultural products, the increase of centralized procurement of agricultural products from core producing areas, the reduction of the cost of selling agricultural products on the platform, and the help of farmers involved in the direct broadcasting of Taobao free of charge.

Thousands of vegetable and fruit greenhouses across the country turned into Taobao live studios on the day, with government representatives and live TV broadcasters also pitching in. Gong Mengqian said that after the release of the special line to help farmers, nails have also exploded, received more than 1500 requests from all over the country to help sell unsalable agricultural products. Put the phone down. She's GonNa go back to selling vegetables.

From time to time, she called Guo Jing and the merchants to follow up on the delivery of goods, must ensure quality. In her eyes, the products, each order, may be behind a family's needs, but also more or less a farmer's heart.

Taobao eat goods internal estimates, each sale of 2000 Jin of agricultural products, you can help a farmer to prepare for the cost of spring rehabilitation. Among the first batch of merchants to log on the "food for farmers" channel, many others have donated vegetables and fruits to the Wuhan epidemic. Taobao eatable goods also appeal to the outside world, hope that more consumers through the way orders to help suffer from poor sales of farmers.

Li Xiaolin is discussing with the villagers recently. Originally these cucumbers must have been smashed, but they could still be sold for money. They feel grateful and want to take some of the vegetables or money to support Wuhan. They are contacting the logistics vehicle. "If the logistics vehicle is available, " We can donate vegetables right now. Anyone who can donate, donate. "

Cheng Kelong thought, after the epidemic ended, oneself want to see oneself once helped also helped own farmer. For the past few days, people have been wearing masks, nodding from a distance, knowing each other's voices, but not knowing what they look like, not even shaking hands, "I just want to see them. " Guo Jing thought, the epidemic is over, life is back to normal, and I do not have to be so tense, must go out, "air, visit, fitness, take the children to a playground. "He hoped that by then, everyone would be able to take off their masks and lead a normal life.
